Hi Andy,

You are on the right track here. The objection would be valid only if
the two pistons were moving in one cylinder. The distance between the
pistons/cylinders means that the transfer is not instantaneous,
therefore there is a pulsating dynamic with localized points of
pressure and vacuum.

John

